Description: An encampment outside Alexandria, plate 1 of four plates; view with three tents along the wall in the foreground, with soldiers resting, further tents in the middle distance, the sea in the background. 1804 Aquatint and etching, printed in dark brown ink
Producer name: Print made by: Frederick Christian Lewis (aquatint)
Associated events: Associated Event: Battle of the Nile August 1-2 1798
